.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR getw ()
readz a word (that is, a \fIint\fP) from \fIstream\fP.
It aint nuthin but provided fo' compatibilitizzle wit SVr4.
We recommend you use
.BR fread (3)
instead.
.P
.BR putw ()
writes tha word \fIw\fP (that is,
an \fIint\fP) ta \fIstream\fP.
It be provided fo' compatibilitizzle wit SVr4 yo, but we recommend you use
.BR fwrite (3)
instead.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Normally,
.BR getw ()
returns tha word read, and
.BR putw ()
returns 0.
On error, they return \fBEOF\fP.
.SH CONFORMING TO
SVr4, SUSv2.  Not present up in POSIX.1-2001.
.SH BUGS
Da value returned on error be also a legitimate data value.
.BR ferror (3)
can be used ta distinguish between tha two cases.
